1
00:00:02,468 --> 00:00:04,969
[ Ukulele Strumming ]

2
00:00:21,120 --> 00:00:23,721
[ Man On TV ]
Ocean Avenue is gearing up
for this year's Lobsterfest,

3
00:00:23,723 --> 00:00:27,792
and that mean old tropical storm
we've been watching is
movin' out to sea,

4
00:00:27,794 --> 00:00:30,428
which means perfect
weekend weather!

5
00:00:30,430 --> 00:00:31,262
Ugh! Damn it!

6
00:00:31,264 --> 00:00:34,465
So if you think
you hear thunder,
it's just my stomach growling.

7
00:00:34,467 --> 00:00:36,300
[ Laughs ]
I love lobster.
[ Laughs ]

8
00:00:36,302 --> 00:00:39,837
This guy is unbelievable.
Stop pimping for Lobsterfest!

9
00:00:39,839 --> 00:00:42,206
And start primping
for Lobsterfest.

10
00:00:42,208 --> 00:00:45,209
Mmm.
[ Growls ]
Looking primpy.

11
00:00:45,211 --> 00:00:46,878
No! No primping for anything!

12
00:00:46,880 --> 00:00:49,547
- Why are you so grumpy?
Come on.
- You know why.

13
00:00:49,549 --> 00:00:52,717
It's no fun
being a burger man
in a seafood town.

14
00:00:52,719 --> 00:00:55,253
I hate lobsters
and their
stupid fest.

15
00:00:55,255 --> 00:00:56,788
Plus, I'm allergic.
No, you're not.

16
00:00:56,790 --> 00:00:58,856
Yeah. I'm allergic.
Remember our first date?

17
00:00:58,858 --> 00:01:02,160
Yeah, I remember our first date.
You were a nervous wreck.

18
00:01:02,162 --> 00:01:04,529
♪ [ Funky Guitar ]

19
00:01:04,531 --> 00:01:07,698
[ Man ]
Ahhh! Uhh!

20
00:01:07,700 --> 00:01:09,167
Oh, yeah.

21
00:01:09,169 --> 00:01:10,802
♪ [ Woman Vocalizing ]

22
00:01:10,804 --> 00:01:13,404
I was having
an allergic reac--
Never mind.

23
00:01:13,406 --> 00:01:15,673
Hey, what are you guys
looking at over there?

24
00:01:15,675 --> 00:01:16,374
Um, nothing.

25
00:01:16,376 --> 00:01:18,743
Just pictures of people--
[ Quietly ]
doing it.

26
00:01:18,745 --> 00:01:20,678
Oh. Hey, wait a minute.
That's not porn.

27
00:01:20,680 --> 00:01:23,481
You brought
a Lobsterfest brochure
into this house?

28
00:01:23,483 --> 00:01:26,217
Can we please go
this year?
Absolutely not.

29
00:01:26,219 --> 00:01:28,519
Ugh! But there's
so much fun stuff happening.

30
00:01:28,521 --> 00:01:31,889
Unveiling of the world's
largest butter vat,
for instance.

31
00:01:31,891 --> 00:01:33,758
The coronation
of the Lobster Queen...

32
00:01:33,760 --> 00:01:35,493
and her court
of lovely lobster maidens.

33
00:01:35,495 --> 00:01:39,864
Entertainment
by John Van Horton
and the Music Extrusion.

34
00:01:39,866 --> 00:01:40,898
Mmm. I do love those guys.

35
00:01:40,900 --> 00:01:44,569
As a matter of fact, Gene,
you were conceived
to a J.V.H. song.

36
00:01:44,571 --> 00:01:46,204
And I plan to return the favor.

37
00:01:46,206 --> 00:01:48,573
- [ Rings ]
- Oh, great.
I mean, hi, Hugo.

38
00:01:48,575 --> 00:01:52,610
I couldn't help but notice,
yours is the only window
on the street...

39
00:01:52,612 --> 00:01:54,579
without a Lobsterfest poster
in it.

40
00:01:54,581 --> 00:01:56,114
Yeah.
Why might that be?

41
00:01:56,116 --> 00:01:57,748
Because Lobsterfest
is stupid!

42
00:01:57,750 --> 00:01:59,484
What?
I'll handle this, Ron.

43
00:01:59,486 --> 00:02:01,219
Put the sign up.
It's the law.

44
00:02:01,221 --> 00:02:02,753
- It's the law?
- Martial law.

45
00:02:02,755 --> 00:02:05,656
I'm Grand Marshal
of the fest this year!

46
00:02:05,658 --> 00:02:07,225
Hugo, such a fancy sash.

47
00:02:07,227 --> 00:02:10,228
You look like Sissy Spacek
in Carrie.
[ Laughs ]

48
00:02:10,230 --> 00:02:12,597
Oh, thank you.
But, Hugo, as a health
inspector,

49
00:02:12,599 --> 00:02:14,866
you must know how disgusting
lobsters are, right?

50
00:02:14,868 --> 00:02:17,268
They're bottom-feeders
that eat garbage all day.

51
00:02:17,270 --> 00:02:19,770
Huh. They like garbage?
Then they must eat here!

52
00:02:19,772 --> 00:02:21,439
[ Laughing ]
In your face, Bob.

53
00:02:21,441 --> 00:02:23,274
And now in your window!
Come on, Ron.

54
00:02:23,276 --> 00:02:27,512
Let's make like a lobster
and get the shell out of here.
All right.

55
00:02:27,514 --> 00:02:29,413
[ Bell Rings ]

56
00:02:30,382 --> 00:02:32,617
- [ Rings ]
- Hey, my two best customers!

57
00:02:32,619 --> 00:02:35,653
- Two burgers coming up.
- No burgers for me, Bob.

58
00:02:35,655 --> 00:02:36,854
I'm saving my appetite
for Lobsterfest.

59
00:02:36,856 --> 00:02:40,525
None for me either, Bobby.
I just come by to show you
my new lobster cracker.

60
00:02:40,527 --> 00:02:43,728
Check it out--
Titanium with
butter-resistant grips.

61
00:02:43,730 --> 00:02:44,729
It's the one
the astronauts used.

62
00:02:44,731 --> 00:02:48,232
Teddy, you think the astronauts
brought a lobster cracker
to space?

63
00:02:48,234 --> 00:02:49,967
Yeah. That's what
it says on the box.
Look.

64
00:02:49,969 --> 00:02:52,970
"The one the astronauts
used in space!"

65
00:02:52,972 --> 00:02:54,472
I spent $49 on this.

66
00:02:54,474 --> 00:02:56,240
Hey, I bet you kids
are old enough...

67
00:02:56,242 --> 00:02:57,909
to crack your own claws
this year, right?

68
00:02:57,911 --> 00:03:00,578
- We don't celebrate
Lobsterfest.
- What?

69
00:03:00,580 --> 00:03:02,446
We're like Jews on Christmas.

70
00:03:02,448 --> 00:03:04,415
Or Jews For Jesus on Hanukkah.

71
00:03:04,417 --> 00:03:06,317
Or me at a lesbian bar...

72
00:03:06,319 --> 00:03:07,285
last night.

73
00:03:07,287 --> 00:03:09,787
Watched a hockey game
at a lesbian bar, Bob.

74
00:03:09,789 --> 00:03:12,490
It was like
I was invisible.

75
00:03:12,492 --> 00:03:13,658
Uh--

76
00:03:15,928 --> 00:03:18,462
And who knows the name
of the delicious paste...

77
00:03:18,464 --> 00:03:20,731
that collects here
in the pancreas?

78
00:03:20,733 --> 00:03:21,699
Tomalley!
Correct.

79
00:03:21,701 --> 00:03:25,503
- [ Clears Throat ]
Excuse me, Miss Labonz?
- Yes, Louise.

80
00:03:25,505 --> 00:03:27,338
My family
doesn't observe Lobsterfest.

81
00:03:27,340 --> 00:03:30,441
I should be
excused from class,
and/or given an "A."

82
00:03:30,443 --> 00:03:31,576
Thank you. Good night.

83
00:03:31,578 --> 00:03:33,411
Louise, I don't normally
use this argument,

84
00:03:33,413 --> 00:03:36,480
but if everyone else
is doing it, you should too.

85
00:03:36,482 --> 00:03:39,850
- [ Thunderclap ]
- [ Grunts ]
Attention, students.

86
00:03:39,852 --> 00:03:41,886
The tropical storm
has changed course,

87
00:03:41,888 --> 00:03:44,021
and has been upgraded
to a hurricane.

88
00:03:44,023 --> 00:03:46,023
It could hit town
at any moment.

89
00:03:46,025 --> 00:03:49,327
Don't worry.
We have an emergency plan.

90
00:03:49,329 --> 00:03:50,761
It's called
"Talking it Through."

91
00:03:50,763 --> 00:03:54,832
Now who here thinks
the hurricane was caused
by something bad they did?

92
00:03:54,834 --> 00:03:56,467
What about you, Nicholas?

93
00:03:56,469 --> 00:03:59,937
That thing you told me?
In confidence?

94
00:04:00,872 --> 00:04:01,973
Say it.

95
00:04:01,975 --> 00:04:04,442
- I rub my genitals
on the couch.
- Mm-hmm.

96
00:04:04,444 --> 00:04:08,045
We're all gonna die
because of you!
[ Students Scream ]

97
00:04:08,047 --> 00:04:10,748
It's weather
only a lobster could love,

98
00:04:10,750 --> 00:04:14,085
but sadly, there will be
no Lobsterfest.

99
00:04:14,087 --> 00:04:16,787
This reporter
is getting his bib off.

100
00:04:16,789 --> 00:04:19,790
Ha, ha!
Stupid, failure weatherman...

101
00:04:19,792 --> 00:04:21,759
and your failed Lobsterfest.

102
00:04:21,761 --> 00:04:25,496
Where's your ugly red
sea bug god now?

103
00:04:25,931 --> 00:04:27,598
All right, hold hands.

104
00:04:27,600 --> 00:04:29,533
Come on,
down to the basement.

105
00:04:29,535 --> 00:04:30,368
Bob, we have to close.

106
00:04:30,370 --> 00:04:34,138
A hurricane is coming!
I know. Isn't it great?

107
00:04:34,140 --> 00:04:35,906
Lobsterfest is canceled!

108
00:04:35,908 --> 00:04:39,343
So this town
is gonna be crawling
with empty bellies...

109
00:04:39,345 --> 00:04:41,779
ready to eat Bob's Burgers,
baby!

110
00:04:41,781 --> 00:04:43,814
Bob, you're crazy.
I think you're crazy!

111
00:04:43,816 --> 00:04:47,618
'Cause it's crazy
not to sell burgers
during a hurricane!

112
00:04:47,620 --> 00:04:50,955
Bob's Burgers
is open for business!

113
00:04:50,957 --> 00:04:53,891
Oh.
[ Crackling ]

114
00:04:53,893 --> 00:04:55,993
Is that all you got, storm?

115
00:04:55,995 --> 00:05:00,564
[ Tinkling ]
Wind chimes! Aaah!

116
00:05:00,566 --> 00:05:03,434
[ Muffled ]

117
00:05:05,971 --> 00:05:08,139
Bob, I'm not sure
staying open is safe.

118
00:05:08,141 --> 00:05:10,675
Suppose the hurricane
tears right through here.

119
00:05:10,677 --> 00:05:11,942
I'll chance it!
[ Bell Rings ]

120
00:05:11,944 --> 00:05:14,945
Look who I found
trying to stay dry
in the bounce house.

121
00:05:14,947 --> 00:05:17,715
The entire royal court
of lobster maidens.

122
00:05:17,717 --> 00:05:19,717
[ Gasps ]
Oh, you poor things!

123
00:05:19,719 --> 00:05:21,018
Welcome,
Your Highnesseses.

124
00:05:21,020 --> 00:05:25,823
Uh, you are henceforth known
as the Royal Cows.
Bob!

125
00:05:25,825 --> 00:05:27,958
Uh, well,
something like that.
[ Chuckles ]

126
00:05:27,960 --> 00:05:29,794
I'll go throw on
some burgers.

127
00:05:29,796 --> 00:05:30,761
Hot coffee coming up!

128
00:05:30,763 --> 00:05:33,831
I'd really rather
get my lips
around that beer tap.

129
00:05:33,833 --> 00:05:36,367
Hi, guys.
Hey, Gretchen!

130
00:05:36,369 --> 00:05:38,869
Hi!
Oh, lobster maiden!

131
00:05:38,871 --> 00:05:40,705
Teddy, this is Gretchen.

132
00:05:40,707 --> 00:05:41,972
She cuts my hair.
How you doing?

133
00:05:41,974 --> 00:05:44,041
Hey, are you still
working nights at the cop bar?

134
00:05:44,043 --> 00:05:46,577
Nah, there was
a groping incident.
[ Gasps ]

135
00:05:46,579 --> 00:05:48,713
I apologized,
but they fired me anyway.

136
00:05:48,715 --> 00:05:51,015
- [ Laughs ]
- Oh, she's too much.

137
00:05:51,017 --> 00:05:52,583
- Really is.
- [ Bell Rings ]

138
00:05:52,585 --> 00:05:54,552
Hey, you open?
Mm-hmm.

139
00:05:54,554 --> 00:05:55,619
- You got food?
- Yup.

140
00:05:55,621 --> 00:05:56,987
- Beer?
- Absolutely!

141
00:05:56,989 --> 00:06:00,491
- Atmosphere?
- Yeah-- N--

142
00:06:00,493 --> 00:06:01,926
Ah, good enough.
Whoa, Bobby.

143
00:06:01,928 --> 00:06:04,895
I think this might develop
into a party-type situation!

144
00:06:04,897 --> 00:06:07,198
You kids stay down
in the basement.

145
00:06:07,200 --> 00:06:09,734
I already picked a corner
for the bathroom.

146
00:06:09,736 --> 00:06:10,768
That one, where I went.

147
00:06:10,770 --> 00:06:13,437
And I picked that corner.
Hey, we've got two bathrooms!

148
00:06:13,439 --> 00:06:15,873
Mom, I'm coming up!
[ Linda ]
Just stay down there.

149
00:06:15,875 --> 00:06:19,643
They're gonna need you
to help repopulate the Earth
when this is all over.

150
00:06:19,645 --> 00:06:22,980
Ew! You want us to mate
with each other?
[ Linda ] No.

151
00:06:22,982 --> 00:06:26,050
You'll mate with the other kids
in other basements.

152
00:06:26,052 --> 00:06:27,051
Keep talking.

153
00:06:27,053 --> 00:06:30,087
All right!
J.V.H. unplugged!

154
00:06:30,089 --> 00:06:31,889
Look at all that
wet gray hair.

155
00:06:31,891 --> 00:06:34,058
Oh, Bobby, look at Hugo.

156
00:06:34,060 --> 00:06:35,926
Oh, and poor wet Ron.

157
00:06:35,928 --> 00:06:37,061
Yeah. Isn't it hilarious?
Bobby.

158
00:06:37,063 --> 00:06:40,898
All right, I'll let 'em in.
I just want to give 'em
a pressed ham first.

159
00:06:40,900 --> 00:06:42,733
- Stop it!
- Come on, let me.

160
00:06:42,735 --> 00:06:44,101
All right.

161
00:06:44,803 --> 00:06:46,704
Sorry for using
all of your napkins.

162
00:06:46,706 --> 00:06:48,906
I want to thank you
for bringing us in, Bob.

163
00:06:48,908 --> 00:06:52,576
It was totally Linda's idea.
She is so damn considerate!

164
00:06:52,578 --> 00:06:54,912
You have everything,
and I have nothing.

165
00:06:54,914 --> 00:06:56,981
God, so alone!
Mmm.
[ Slurps ]

166
00:06:56,983 --> 00:07:00,050
Lobsterfest was all I had,
and now that's gone too.

167
00:07:00,052 --> 00:07:02,586
Look at me. I'm a joke!
Yeah, that's too bad.

168
00:07:02,588 --> 00:07:04,622
Hey, Bobby, some
of the lobster maidens...

169
00:07:04,624 --> 00:07:07,124
are open to the idea
of a wet-gown contest.

170
00:07:07,126 --> 00:07:08,192
Want to put up a prize?

171
00:07:08,194 --> 00:07:11,228
Uh, how about a towel?
[ Laughs ]
Oh, my God.

172
00:07:11,230 --> 00:07:12,897
That's so funny.
[ Laughs ]

173
00:07:12,899 --> 00:07:14,265
Gretchen, have you,
uh, met Hugo?

174
00:07:14,267 --> 00:07:17,568
He was gonna be
Grand Marshal at,
uh, Lobsterfest.

175
00:07:17,570 --> 00:07:18,969
Ooh. Nice sash.

176
00:07:18,971 --> 00:07:21,238
Ever take it off?
Well, actually, on Monday...

177
00:07:21,240 --> 00:07:23,574
I have to dry-clean it
and give it back.

178
00:07:23,576 --> 00:07:25,776
Hugo, Gretchen
is into authority figures.

179
00:07:25,778 --> 00:07:30,047
Cops, firemen--
even mailmen, if they have
an important route.

180
00:07:30,049 --> 00:07:30,948
Oh, my gosh. So am I!

181
00:07:30,950 --> 00:07:33,551
What, you're into mailmen?
Well, if they have
an important route.

182
00:07:33,553 --> 00:07:37,154
I think what Bob's saying is,
she likes a man
with a badge.

183
00:07:37,156 --> 00:07:38,823
You have a badge.
Hey, Gretchen!

184
00:07:38,825 --> 00:07:41,625
Huh?
Hey, Hugo's also
a health inspector.

185
00:07:41,627 --> 00:07:43,561
That's like
being a food sheriff.

186
00:07:43,563 --> 00:07:46,864
This is my badge.
Mmm. Kind of small.

187
00:07:46,866 --> 00:07:48,566
You got a gun?
Uh, no.

188
00:07:48,568 --> 00:07:50,134
Actually, I'm not, uh--
Mmm.

189
00:07:50,136 --> 00:07:51,168
licensed to carry a firearm.

190
00:07:51,170 --> 00:07:53,838
I do have
a food safety thermometer,
and it's very sharp.

191
00:07:53,840 --> 00:07:56,841
Pull it out, Hugo.
Yeah, pull it out,
Hugo.

192
00:07:56,843 --> 00:07:58,742
[ Laughing ]
Whoa! Watch out.

193
00:07:58,744 --> 00:08:00,544
Here it is.
Ooh.

194
00:08:00,546 --> 00:08:01,812
"Unsafe range."

195
00:08:01,814 --> 00:08:04,682
I like my pork
a little pink.

196
00:08:04,684 --> 00:08:06,851
♪ [ Funky Guitar ]

197
00:08:06,853 --> 00:08:10,154
[ Man ]
Ahhh! Uhh!

198
00:08:10,156 --> 00:08:11,555
Oh, yeah!

199
00:08:11,557 --> 00:08:13,290
Mmm.
Tina,
what are you doing?

200
00:08:13,292 --> 00:08:14,959
I'm working
on my mating list...

201
00:08:14,961 --> 00:08:16,994
for when we have to repopulate
the world.

202
00:08:16,996 --> 00:08:19,196
Let me see.
Gay. Gay.

203
00:08:19,198 --> 00:08:22,633
Mythical creature.
Gay mythical creature.

204
00:08:22,635 --> 00:08:23,734
Mmm. Good luck.

205
00:08:23,736 --> 00:08:27,004
Guys, we're wasting time here.
We gotta sneak out.

206
00:08:27,006 --> 00:08:29,807
Sneak out?
But there's a hurricane.
That's my point.

207
00:08:29,809 --> 00:08:34,311
We should be out there,
in the wind and rain, looting!
Looting?

208
00:08:34,313 --> 00:08:37,648
So how do we do this
looting thing exactly?

209
00:08:37,650 --> 00:08:40,851
It's easy.
You grab anything
that's not nailed down.

210
00:08:40,853 --> 00:08:42,953
Anything?
Like this brick?

211
00:08:42,955 --> 00:08:44,989
It's yours.
Free brick!

212
00:08:44,991 --> 00:08:47,057
- Free quarter.
- Free phone numbers.

213
00:08:47,059 --> 00:08:50,127
- Free seaweed.
- Gene, free plywood.

214
00:08:50,129 --> 00:08:51,295
Whee!

215
00:08:51,297 --> 00:08:53,831
Hey, Bob, the cash register
won't open,

216
00:08:53,833 --> 00:08:55,366
and you're serving
burgers so fast,

217
00:08:55,368 --> 00:08:57,167
I don't even know
who to get an I.O.U. from.

218
00:08:57,169 --> 00:08:59,603
Relax, Linda.
I'll take care of it.
[ Groans ]

219
00:08:59,605 --> 00:09:02,606
Hey, hey, hey, hey.
Listen up, listen up.

220
00:09:02,608 --> 00:09:04,208
You're all my friends,

221
00:09:04,210 --> 00:09:07,111
and friends don't
charge friends.

222
00:09:07,113 --> 00:09:09,146
The burgers are free,
people!
[ Cheering ]

223
00:09:09,148 --> 00:09:10,347
Everything is gonna be free!

224
00:09:10,349 --> 00:09:14,919
Bob, I thought the point
of staying open during
a hurricane was to make money!

225
00:09:14,921 --> 00:09:17,955
This is way more important
than money, Lin!

226
00:09:17,957 --> 00:09:19,957
Lobsterfest is dead.

227
00:09:19,959 --> 00:09:21,158
Bobsterfest killed it!

228
00:09:21,160 --> 00:09:26,330
[ Cheering ]
[ Man ]
Long live Bobsterfest!

229
00:09:26,332 --> 00:09:27,331
Looting is hard.

230
00:09:27,333 --> 00:09:29,300
[ Sighs ]
I think I'm getting
loot glutes.

231
00:09:29,302 --> 00:09:33,370
This stuff sucks.
Let's go home.

232
00:09:33,372 --> 00:09:34,838
Hello!

233
00:09:34,840 --> 00:09:36,373
What have we here?

234
00:09:36,375 --> 00:09:39,076
Maybe he's lost.
Check his collar.

235
00:09:39,078 --> 00:09:39,743
Get him, Gene!

236
00:09:39,745 --> 00:09:43,180
Looks like this little guy
got into some
office supplies.

237
00:09:43,182 --> 00:09:46,083
Yeah, those rubber bands
don't look comfortable.

238
00:09:46,085 --> 00:09:48,352
You should take 'em off.

239
00:09:48,354 --> 00:09:48,986
Aaah!

240
00:09:48,988 --> 00:09:52,690
This is our one chance
to see what everyone else
is talking about.

241
00:09:52,692 --> 00:09:53,958
What do you mean?
Aaah!

242
00:09:53,960 --> 00:09:54,992
We're gonna eat lobster tonight!

243
00:09:54,994 --> 00:09:57,695
But that goes against
everything we were raised
to believe in!

244
00:09:57,697 --> 00:10:00,364
Aaah!
It doesn't
go against everything.

245
00:10:00,366 --> 00:10:02,099
Okay? But it's a start.
Aaah!

246
00:10:02,101 --> 00:10:05,069
Now's our chance to taste
the forbidden fruit...

247
00:10:05,071 --> 00:10:07,972
that has been kept from us
our whole lives.

248
00:10:07,974 --> 00:10:09,607
Are you with me?

249
00:10:09,609 --> 00:10:10,341
Yeah!
Okay.

250
00:10:10,343 --> 00:10:15,980
And one man's generosity
has turned Lobsterfest
into Bobsterfest.

251
00:10:15,982 --> 00:10:18,182
We're trying to get a word
with Bob himself here.

252
00:10:18,184 --> 00:10:21,218
[ Slurring ]
I love you, Scott Bags!

253
00:10:21,220 --> 00:10:23,087
[ Chuckles ]
Yeah, there's
a cable on that.

254
00:10:23,089 --> 00:10:25,155
You can't go over there.
You come with me!

255
00:10:25,157 --> 00:10:26,790
Yeah, okay.
You come with me!

256
00:10:26,792 --> 00:10:28,092
Can I get
my mic back, please?

257
00:10:28,094 --> 00:10:29,927
You come up and get it.
Give me the mic!

258
00:10:29,929 --> 00:10:32,463
- [ Chanting ]
Bob! Bob! Bob!
- Whoa! Oh, wow!

259
00:10:32,465 --> 00:10:33,764
This feels weird!

260
00:10:33,766 --> 00:10:38,402
- Hey, bro.
- Did I hook you up
or what, Hugo?

261
00:10:38,404 --> 00:10:39,303
Whoo!

262
00:10:39,305 --> 00:10:41,005
Hey, where are we going now?
Over here?

263
00:10:41,007 --> 00:10:45,342
Who decides which way we go?
There's Linda, my wife!

264
00:10:45,344 --> 00:10:47,378
Hey, Linda, you look mad.

265
00:10:47,380 --> 00:10:49,913
Let's go the other way.
Turn around.

266
00:10:49,915 --> 00:10:52,416
Bye, Linda.

267
00:10:54,686 --> 00:10:56,153
How you feeling, Bob?

268
00:10:56,155 --> 00:10:57,421
[ Groans ]
What?

269
00:10:57,423 --> 00:11:00,290
Oh, my God. Lin!
The restaurant's destroyed.

270
00:11:00,292 --> 00:11:02,760
The hurricane swept
right through here.
We got hit!

271
00:11:02,762 --> 00:11:04,895
Actually, the hurricane
missed us, Bob.

272
00:11:04,897 --> 00:11:06,797
[ Birds Twittering ]
It's beautiful out.

273
00:11:06,799 --> 00:11:09,066
♪ [ Humming ]
Hmm.

274
00:11:09,068 --> 00:11:12,136
You were the hurricane,
schmuck!

275
00:11:12,804 --> 00:11:15,773
[ Groans ]
Hey, Gretchen.

276
00:11:15,775 --> 00:11:18,942
Do you have some sweat pants
I can put on?

277
00:11:21,346 --> 00:11:24,048
[ Groaning ]
Linda.

278
00:11:24,050 --> 00:11:25,382
Uh, Linda.

279
00:11:25,384 --> 00:11:27,384
I don't feel well.
I can't even look at you.

280
00:11:27,386 --> 00:11:29,286
I don't feel well.
I did this?

281
00:11:29,288 --> 00:11:33,490
You and the mob you incited
with free beer and burgers.

282
00:11:33,492 --> 00:11:35,926
Oh, who bent
my little spindle thing?

283
00:11:35,928 --> 00:11:37,294
That's what you notice?

284
00:11:37,296 --> 00:11:38,929
Okay, Lin,
it looks bad now,

285
00:11:38,931 --> 00:11:41,198
but we made a lot
of new friends last night.

286
00:11:41,200 --> 00:11:43,333
Once word spreads
that Bob needs help,

287
00:11:43,335 --> 00:11:44,401
this place
will be jammed again.

288
00:11:44,403 --> 00:11:48,338
The biggest problem
is gonna be finding a job
for everybody who wants one.

289
00:11:48,340 --> 00:11:51,241
Do you remember
where we bought this?
I really love it.

290
00:11:51,243 --> 00:11:54,778
♪ [ Funky Guitar ]
[ Man ]
Ahhh!

291
00:11:54,780 --> 00:11:59,383
Okay, technical problems
from last night
have been resolved.

292
00:11:59,385 --> 00:12:03,187
Hair dryer plus waffle iron
plus toaster...

293
00:12:03,189 --> 00:12:04,888
equals boiling water.

294
00:12:04,890 --> 00:12:07,124
So how do we kill this guy
before we boil him?

295
00:12:07,126 --> 00:12:08,792
We could teach
the lobster to drive...

296
00:12:08,794 --> 00:12:10,394
and wait until
it gets into an accident.

297
00:12:10,396 --> 00:12:12,830
Orwe could hire an assassin.

298
00:12:12,832 --> 00:12:15,265
No, idiots,
you boil lobsters alive.

299
00:12:15,267 --> 00:12:17,735
What? That doesn't sound right.

300
00:12:17,737 --> 00:12:19,069
Yep. Until he's dead.

301
00:12:19,071 --> 00:12:22,106
And then we boil him
some more.
Here we go.

302
00:12:22,108 --> 00:12:23,841
Wait, this doesn't
feel right.

303
00:12:23,843 --> 00:12:26,877
Doing it in a dark room
with toilet paper
around my neck?

304
00:12:26,879 --> 00:12:29,046
I thought my first time
eating lobster
would be special.

305
00:12:29,048 --> 00:12:32,349
[ Man ]
And now please join
Mr. and Mrs. Jimmy Jr....

306
00:12:32,351 --> 00:12:36,019
as they eat their
first lobster!
Mmm, mmm.

307
00:12:36,021 --> 00:12:36,386
Mmm. Mmm.

308
00:12:36,388 --> 00:12:39,323
I thought my first time
eating lobster
would be different too.

309
00:12:39,325 --> 00:12:41,391
[ Crowd Chanting ]
Gene! Gene! Gene!
[ Gene Farting ]

310
00:12:41,393 --> 00:12:46,029
They're waiting for you
in the hot tub, Gene.
Excellent!

311
00:12:46,031 --> 00:12:48,098
Whee!
[ Chomping ]

312
00:12:48,100 --> 00:12:52,336
And the next day do it again--
same songs, different lobsters.

313
00:12:52,338 --> 00:12:54,304
What's the matter
with you two?

314
00:12:54,306 --> 00:12:55,005
Come on, Louise.

315
00:12:55,007 --> 00:12:57,574
Is this really
how you imagined
your first time?

316
00:12:57,576 --> 00:12:58,609
Yes.

317
00:12:58,611 --> 00:13:00,444
[ Sighs ]
Okay, not quite.

318
00:13:00,446 --> 00:13:04,848
[ Man ]
Louise, today you pay
the super price...

319
00:13:04,850 --> 00:13:07,251
for your super crimes.

320
00:13:07,253 --> 00:13:09,119
Enjoy your last meal.

321
00:13:09,121 --> 00:13:11,889
It'll do just fine--
in a pinch!

322
00:13:11,891 --> 00:13:14,024
[ Both Screaming ]

323
00:13:14,026 --> 00:13:15,626
Maybe we have
been rushing things.

324
00:13:15,628 --> 00:13:18,495
I want to wait till
I'm ready. Let's not
give in to peer pressure.

325
00:13:18,497 --> 00:13:23,267
Let's release the lobster
back into the supermarket
from whence he came!

326
00:13:23,269 --> 00:13:24,101
I guess you're right.

327
00:13:24,103 --> 00:13:27,905
Looks like this guy's
the one that got a--
Oh, whoops!

328
00:13:28,573 --> 00:13:30,541
I guess we're
having lobster.
It was meant to be.

329
00:13:30,543 --> 00:13:34,978
When you get married,
just pretend it's your
first time eating lobster.

330
00:13:34,980 --> 00:13:36,547
No problem.

331
00:13:36,549 --> 00:13:37,614
[ Man On P.A. ]
Down it comes!

332
00:13:37,616 --> 00:13:40,250
This stunning butter sculpture,
the likeness of Julia Child,

333
00:13:40,252 --> 00:13:42,986
was made from every available
stick and pat of butter...

334
00:13:42,988 --> 00:13:45,122
within the local
and outlying communities.

335
00:13:45,124 --> 00:13:47,090
Oh! And there goes Julia's feet!

336
00:13:47,092 --> 00:13:49,126
What? Lobsterfest is back on?

337
00:13:49,128 --> 00:13:53,964
Hey, guys, um,
you're not going
to Lobsterfest, are you?

338
00:13:53,966 --> 00:13:55,199
Uh--
Uh--

339
00:13:55,201 --> 00:13:56,967
I'm in kind of a bind, fellas.

340
00:13:56,969 --> 00:13:59,303
There's a mailbox
in the middle of my restaurant.

341
00:13:59,305 --> 00:14:01,405
Oh! Can you mail this
for me?

342
00:14:01,407 --> 00:14:03,006
Wait. Hey, guys?

343
00:14:03,008 --> 00:14:05,442
There he is, my buddy, Hugo!

344
00:14:05,444 --> 00:14:06,977
Hi.
Oh, hi, Bob.

345
00:14:06,979 --> 00:14:09,012
Hi, Bobby.
What are you both
doing right now?

346
00:14:09,014 --> 00:14:12,916
My, uh, place, uh,
happened to get destroyed
last night.

347
00:14:12,918 --> 00:14:14,017
Oh, really?
Yeah.

348
00:14:14,019 --> 00:14:15,385
In the middle of--
Bob, I'm very busy.

349
00:14:15,387 --> 00:14:17,921
I have tables and tables
of bisque to judge.

350
00:14:17,923 --> 00:14:19,022
Hey, I hooked you two up
last night,

351
00:14:19,024 --> 00:14:22,392
and you guys kind of broke
the baby-changing station
in the bathroom.

352
00:14:22,394 --> 00:14:24,962
[ Chuckles ]
Slap him
with a citation, Hugo.

353
00:14:24,964 --> 00:14:26,964
I want to watch.
Baby likes civil authority?

354
00:14:26,966 --> 00:14:29,900
Yes, I love civil authority.
I'll show baby civil authority.

355
00:14:29,902 --> 00:14:32,636
Stilts guy!
You fell through my window.

356
00:14:32,638 --> 00:14:34,338
Lot of glass on the floor.

357
00:14:34,340 --> 00:14:36,106
Where you going?
Got to go, Bob!

358
00:14:36,108 --> 00:14:39,042
If I stay still too long,
I fall over!

359
00:14:39,044 --> 00:14:41,478
P-People! Wait! Stop!

360
00:14:41,480 --> 00:14:42,512
Wait! People!

361
00:14:42,514 --> 00:14:45,349
Do you think you can
just ignore me?

362
00:14:45,351 --> 00:14:46,049
[ Both Slurping ]

363
00:14:46,051 --> 00:14:50,520
Well, as far
as accidental death goes,
this one was pretty tasty.

364
00:14:50,522 --> 00:14:52,456
I feel tingly.
Do you feel tingly?

365
00:14:52,458 --> 00:14:55,993
I think he's having
an allergic reaction.
We should do something.

366
00:14:55,995 --> 00:14:58,462
Yeah, let's sit on him
and see if he pops.

367
00:14:58,464 --> 00:14:59,329
[ Shouts ]
[ Groans ]

368
00:14:59,331 --> 00:15:02,666
No, we should take him
to Lobsterfest.
They have a medical tent.

369
00:15:02,668 --> 00:15:04,568
And I could get more lobster!

370
00:15:04,570 --> 00:15:07,404
Oh, pop!
I'm trying!

371
00:15:07,406 --> 00:15:12,309
Let's hear it
for John Van Horton
and the Music Extrusion!

372
00:15:12,311 --> 00:15:14,411
Uh, it's me. Bob!

373
00:15:14,413 --> 00:15:17,214
- [ Man Shouting ]
Lobsterfest rocks!
- Bob. Bob.

374
00:15:17,216 --> 00:15:19,616
- Bob.
- [ Man ]
Get off the stage!

375
00:15:19,618 --> 00:15:20,550
[ Chuckling ]
Okay, settle down.

376
00:15:20,552 --> 00:15:24,054
Listen, what's going on here?
What are we doing?
♪ [ Guitar Tuning ]

377
00:15:24,056 --> 00:15:28,692
Last thing I remember,
you were all in my place
and it was Bobsterfest.

378
00:15:28,694 --> 00:15:32,496
I want to get back to that.
Let's go back to that!

379
00:15:32,498 --> 00:15:33,630
Or at the very least,

380
00:15:33,632 --> 00:15:36,199
40 or 50 of you
come with me right now...

381
00:15:36,201 --> 00:15:38,268
and help me clean up
the restaurant!

382
00:15:38,270 --> 00:15:40,337
♪ [ Guitar: Sour Note ]
Not all at once.

383
00:15:40,339 --> 00:15:41,605
[ Man ]
Clean it yourself!

384
00:15:41,607 --> 00:15:43,774
Whoa, Dad's on the stage
at Lobsterfest.

385
00:15:43,776 --> 00:15:47,210
My eyes don't work.
Paint me a word picture.

386
00:15:47,212 --> 00:15:48,345
Kids? What are you doing here?

387
00:15:48,347 --> 00:15:51,348
- Nothing.
- What's wrong with Gene?
He looks horrible.

388
00:15:51,350 --> 00:15:54,518
- He looks like
he always looks.
- No, he doesn't. Does he?

389
00:15:54,520 --> 00:15:58,355
Looks like an allergic--
[ Gasps ]
Did you eat lobster?

390
00:15:58,357 --> 00:16:00,757
I, uh--
He refuses
to answer that.

391
00:16:00,759 --> 00:16:02,793
What's wrong with you people?

392
00:16:02,795 --> 00:16:04,661
- Look at my son!
- Hello.

393
00:16:04,663 --> 00:16:09,333
You did this!
You and your disgusting
food fetish!

394
00:16:09,335 --> 00:16:11,468
Bob, get off the stage.
You're disorderly.

395
00:16:11,470 --> 00:16:16,173
Oh, yeah?
Maybe I should get disorderly
with this lobster pot here.

396
00:16:16,175 --> 00:16:17,541
That's right, you heard me--

397
00:16:17,543 --> 00:16:19,977
You trash my restaurant,
I trash Lobsterfest--

398
00:16:19,979 --> 00:16:21,144
starting with this lobster pot.

399
00:16:21,146 --> 00:16:24,047
[ Sizzles ]
Ow! It's hot.
Let's leave that alone.

400
00:16:24,049 --> 00:16:25,048
Oh, but I-I see some butter.

401
00:16:25,050 --> 00:16:28,618
You wouldn't like it
if someone messed
with your precious butter!

402
00:16:28,620 --> 00:16:30,754
Like stuff a big,
hairy toe in it!

403
00:16:30,756 --> 00:16:33,523
Bob, put your foot back
in your sock slowly.

404
00:16:33,525 --> 00:16:39,096
I'm authorizing myself to use
my brand-new beanbag gun
to subdue you.

405
00:16:39,098 --> 00:16:41,631
Excuse me. I'm sorry.
Excuse me. excuse me.

406
00:16:41,633 --> 00:16:44,468
Bob! No! This isn't you!

407
00:16:44,470 --> 00:16:46,069
This is me, Linda!

408
00:16:46,071 --> 00:16:48,171
This is the me that they made.

409
00:16:48,173 --> 00:16:50,407
And look what they did
to our son.

410
00:16:50,409 --> 00:16:52,676
That's not
how he normally looks, is it?

411
00:16:52,678 --> 00:16:53,810
Bobby, listen to me.

412
00:16:53,812 --> 00:16:55,212
Excuse me. I'm sorry.
Oh, sorry.

413
00:16:55,214 --> 00:16:56,747
You don't have
to keep moving!

414
00:16:56,749 --> 00:16:59,683
You're not a bottom-feeder, Bob!

415
00:17:00,718 --> 00:17:04,187
No, I'm not a bottom-feeder.

416
00:17:04,189 --> 00:17:05,455
I'm a burger man.

417
00:17:05,457 --> 00:17:08,692
[ Sniffles ]
All right, I'm leaving.

418
00:17:08,694 --> 00:17:11,161
I'm sure that's
what everybody wants.

419
00:17:11,163 --> 00:17:14,564
- Oh, what happens if I--
Oh, whoops!
- Ow!

420
00:17:14,566 --> 00:17:16,099
Ow!

421
00:17:16,101 --> 00:17:17,701
[ Crowd Exclaims, Murmurs ]

422
00:17:17,703 --> 00:17:21,171
Bobby, are you okay?
Excuse me. Uh, excuse me.

423
00:17:22,507 --> 00:17:23,540
Oh, my God!

424
00:17:23,542 --> 00:17:25,375
All the butter's
been contaminated by Bob,

425
00:17:25,377 --> 00:17:27,778
and there isn't any more
in town!

426
00:17:27,780 --> 00:17:29,279
Aaah!

427
00:17:30,815 --> 00:17:33,483
[ Chattering ]

428
00:17:33,485 --> 00:17:34,751
Bob destroyed Lobsterfest!

429
00:17:34,753 --> 00:17:37,687
Can't you just eat lobster
without butter?

430
00:17:37,689 --> 00:17:39,222
[ Crowd Shouts ]

431
00:17:39,224 --> 00:17:40,891
Well, why don't you
call it Butterfest?

432
00:17:40,893 --> 00:17:43,293
- It brings out
the succulence, jerk!
- Yeah!

433
00:17:43,295 --> 00:17:46,396
- So what should we do with him?
- Throw him in the shell pile!

434
00:17:46,398 --> 00:17:49,399
- Shell pile?
- [ Muffled ]
Shell pile! Shell pile!

435
00:17:49,401 --> 00:17:52,369
[ Chanting ]
Shell pile! Shell pile!
Shell pile! Shell pile!

436
00:17:52,371 --> 00:17:55,272
- Oh, boy.
- Excuse me. Excuse me. Sorry.

437
00:17:55,274 --> 00:17:57,307
Maybe Bob shouldn't have
threatened your butter,

438
00:17:57,309 --> 00:18:00,877
and he definitely
should have charged you
for the burgers--

439
00:18:00,879 --> 00:18:01,678
[ Booing ]

440
00:18:01,680 --> 00:18:04,548
but he opened
his beautiful heart last night,

441
00:18:04,550 --> 00:18:07,350
and you boiled it alive
like a lobster!

442
00:18:07,352 --> 00:18:09,453
All you're doing
is making us hungrier!

443
00:18:09,455 --> 00:18:11,521
- Shell pile!
- Shell pile!

444
00:18:11,523 --> 00:18:13,623
Sorry, Bobby.
I used a bad analogy.

445
00:18:13,625 --> 00:18:14,658
Hugo, this doesn't
seem right.

446
00:18:14,660 --> 00:18:18,595
What? I have a girlfriend;
Bob's about to be thrown
onto a shell pile--

447
00:18:18,597 --> 00:18:20,730
I've had this exact fantasy.

448
00:18:20,732 --> 00:18:21,898
[ Ron ]
Come on, Hugo.

449
00:18:21,900 --> 00:18:24,301
If Bob hadn't been
your wingman last night,

450
00:18:24,303 --> 00:18:27,204
you'd be another lonely guy
in a satin sash.

451
00:18:27,206 --> 00:18:28,538
I was doing fine!

452
00:18:28,540 --> 00:18:31,408
I don't need a wingman!

453
00:18:31,410 --> 00:18:33,343
Oh, no?

454
00:18:34,245 --> 00:18:37,681
[ Ron ]
♪ Wingman,
flying with the eagles ♪

455
00:18:37,683 --> 00:18:41,284
♪ Wingman,
he's trying to help you out ♪

456
00:18:41,286 --> 00:18:44,588
♪ Wingman, Wingman

457
00:18:44,590 --> 00:18:47,791
♪ Wingman, Wingman

458
00:18:47,793 --> 00:18:49,826
♪ Wingman

459
00:18:49,828 --> 00:18:51,528
[ Groans ]
Damn it, Ron!

460
00:18:51,530 --> 00:18:53,396
All right, attention,
people!

461
00:18:53,398 --> 00:18:55,799
Stop it, everyone!
Slow down!

462
00:18:55,801 --> 00:18:56,867
I'm the health inspector.

463
00:18:56,869 --> 00:19:00,637
Someone once told me
that's like being
the food sheriff.

464
00:19:00,639 --> 00:19:05,342
This vat of butter
isn't contaminated by Bob
until I say so!

465
00:19:05,344 --> 00:19:08,778
I have with me
a dairy purity spectrometer.

466
00:19:08,780 --> 00:19:11,414
- Oh!
- Now, give me some room.

467
00:19:11,416 --> 00:19:13,150
Give him some room!

468
00:19:13,152 --> 00:19:15,252
Thank you, Gretchen.

469
00:19:15,553 --> 00:19:16,820
Ow! You stabbed me!

470
00:19:16,822 --> 00:19:19,923
That's just epinephrine.
You're in anaphylactic shock.

471
00:19:19,925 --> 00:19:21,625
Mm, you're a handsome shrimp.

472
00:19:21,627 --> 00:19:23,460
You just jumped
to the top of my list.

473
00:19:23,462 --> 00:19:25,362
It's a mating list
for when the world ends.

474
00:19:25,364 --> 00:19:26,796
Can I get your e-mail?
No.

475
00:19:26,798 --> 00:19:30,133
I have finished
my butter analysis.

476
00:19:31,202 --> 00:19:35,305
Bob's skin flakes, arm hair
and fingernail dirt
are all present.

477
00:19:35,307 --> 00:19:38,308
- [ Together ]
No!
- Let me finish!

478
00:19:38,310 --> 00:19:41,411
They're present,
but not at threatening levels.

479
00:19:41,413 --> 00:19:43,280
The butter
is grade "C" to D-minus.

480
00:19:43,282 --> 00:19:47,551
Fit for everyone
except babies and people
with compromised immune systems.

481
00:19:47,553 --> 00:19:50,320
In other words, get your bib on!

482
00:19:50,322 --> 00:19:52,722
[ Cheering ]

483
00:19:53,658 --> 00:19:55,692
Man, that was
the best Lobsterfest ever.

484
00:19:55,694 --> 00:20:00,797
Yeah. Turns out people
are hard on the outside
and soft on the inside.

485
00:20:00,799 --> 00:20:02,732
Like, uh--

486
00:20:02,734 --> 00:20:04,701
Like, uh--

487
00:20:04,703 --> 00:20:05,902
Uh--

488
00:20:05,904 --> 00:20:08,772
Oh, I don't know.
Like a-- like a crab.

489
00:20:08,774 --> 00:20:10,840
Yup. People are just like crabs.

490
00:20:10,842 --> 00:20:12,809
And we witnessed the birth
of a new tradition--

491
00:20:12,811 --> 00:20:16,746
Every year on Lobsterfest Eve,
we trash Bob's place.
No, no, no, no.

492
00:20:16,748 --> 00:20:18,415
Right?
Let's start now!

493
00:20:18,417 --> 00:20:21,585
Gene, you swear
you didn't have lobster?

494
00:20:21,587 --> 00:20:23,286
You've always
looked like this?

495
00:20:23,288 --> 00:20:24,588
I was born like this.

496
00:20:24,590 --> 00:20:26,957
Uh, I need a picture to compare.

497
00:20:26,959 --> 00:20:27,724
Oh, my God.

498
00:20:27,726 --> 00:20:30,961
You do always look like this.
[ Gene, Muffled ]
Hello, gorgeous!

499
00:20:30,963 --> 00:20:32,462
[ Growls ]
[ Bell Rings ]

500
00:20:32,464 --> 00:20:36,266
Bob, Linda.
Hey, Hugo.
Where's Gretchen?

501
00:20:36,268 --> 00:20:37,834
She's a firecracker,
that Gretchen.

502
00:20:37,836 --> 00:20:40,570
You sure she's
not more than
you can handle, Hugo?

503
00:20:40,572 --> 00:20:41,972
Gretchen just
broke up with me.

504
00:20:41,974 --> 00:20:44,341
She said she was more
than I could handle.

505
00:20:44,343 --> 00:20:45,475
Oh.
It was ugly.

506
00:20:45,477 --> 00:20:47,711
She said she didn't mind
a small badge,

507
00:20:47,713 --> 00:20:50,914
but said I didn't know how
to use it, Bob!

508
00:20:50,916 --> 00:20:52,315
[ Together ]
Ouch.

509
00:20:52,317 --> 00:20:53,683
Oh, that's too bad.

510
00:20:53,685 --> 00:20:55,518
I don't need your pity!

511
00:20:55,520 --> 00:21:00,290
- So! Here we are.
Surprise inspection!
- Oh.

512
00:21:00,292 --> 00:21:01,691
Pencil!
[ Ron ]
Pencil.

513
00:21:01,693 --> 00:21:02,392
Pad!
Pad.

514
00:21:02,394 --> 00:21:05,662
Ooh, bent spindle.
Ron! Shut it down!

515
00:21:05,664 --> 00:21:07,998
[ Lobsterfest Announcer ]
Let's here it
for John Van Horton...

516
00:21:08,000 --> 00:21:11,334
and the Music Extrusion!
[ Man ]
Check.

517
00:21:11,336 --> 00:21:15,372
♪ [ Drumroll ]
[ Amplifier Feedback ]

518
00:21:16,440 --> 00:21:18,041
♪ [ Electric Guitar Tuning ]

519
00:21:18,043 --> 00:21:19,943
[ Man ]
It's this one here!
[ Feedback Continues ]

520
00:21:19,945 --> 00:21:21,878
[ Man #2,
Indistinct ]
It's this one.

521
00:21:21,880 --> 00:21:24,981
Turn it off!
Turn it off!

522
00:21:24,983 --> 00:21:27,450
[ Feedback Stops ]

523
00:21:28,085 --> 00:21:30,453
[ Man #3 ]
You suck!

524
00:21:31,522 --> 00:21:33,657
♪ [ Guitar
Chord ]
Play something!

525
00:21:33,659 --> 00:21:36,826
[ Man #1 ]
One, two,
three, four!

